Regex Data Extraction

A simple tool for extracting common data patterns from text files using regular expressions.

What it does

This script searches through text and finds:
- Email addresses
- URLs  
- Phone numbers
- Credit card numbers
- Currency amounts
- Time formats
- HTML tags

Getting started

Clone the repo and run the script:


git clone https://github.com/kbelyse/alu_regex-data-extraction-kbelyse.git
cd alu_regex-data-extraction-kbelyse
python3 regex_extractor.py


To process your own files:

python3 regex_extractor.py myfile.txt
or

python3 regex_extractor.py webpage.html

Examples

When you run the script, it'll show what it found:

=== EXTRACTION RESULTS ===

EMAIL matches (2 found):
----------------------------------------
  • user@example.com
  • firstname.lastname@company.co.uk

URL matches (2 found):
----------------------------------------
  • https://www.example.com
  • https://subdomain.example.org/page


Notes

- Works with any text-based file
- No extra libraries needed
- Some patterns are focused on US formats (like phone numbers)
